NNAAMMEE
       grog - guess options for groff command

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ggrroogg [ --_o_p_t_i_o_n ...  ] [ _f_i_l_e_s...  ]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       ggrroogg reads _f_i_l_e_s and guesses which of the ggrrooffff(1) options
       --ee, --mmaann, --mmee, --mmmm, --mmss, --pp, --ss, and --tt are  required  for
       printing  _f_i_l_e_s,  and  prints  the groff command including
       those options on the standard output.  A filename of --  is
       taken  to  refer  to  the standard input.  If no files are
       specified the standard input will be read.  Any  specified
       options will be included in the printed command.  No space
       is allowed between options and their arguments.  For exam-
       ple,

              ``ggrroogg --TTddvvii ppaappeerr..mmss``

       will  guess  the  approriate command to print ppaappeerr..mmss and
       then run it after adding the --TTddvvii option.

